INSERT INTO `author` VALUES
    (1,'1002',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/mahatma-gandhi.jpg','authors/mohandas-karamchand-gandhi','Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi','Gandhi was born to an influential family in a small coastal town that was part of British-ruled India. He was married at age 13 in an arranged marriage per local custom. The couple would bear five children, though their first child only survived a few days. Gandhi left India in 1888 to study law in London, England, and from age 24 to 45, Gandhi became involved in the civil rights movement in South Africa, combating injustice against Indians in the country. He returned to India in 1915 and became the leader of the Indian National Congress and of the struggle for Indian independence from Britain. In 1947, India was finally released from British rule. Gandhi was assassinated by Nathuram Godse in 1948.'),
    (2,'0326',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/robert-frost.jpg','authors/robert-frost','Robert Frost','The son of a journalist and a teacher, Robert Frost grew up in San Francisco, California and Lawrence Massachusetts, publishing his first poem in his high school magazine. In 1894, he sold his first poem, “My butterfly, An Elegy,” and proposed marriage to Elinor Miriam White. She initially rejected him but later agreed and the two married in 1895. Frost worked as a farmer in New Hampshire for nine years, writing poetry in the mornings. He later returned to teaching and published his first and most notable book of poetry, A Boy’s Will, in 1913. He continued a long career of teaching and writing, winning four Pulitzer Prizes for his poetry.'),
    (3,'1130',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/02/winston-churchill.jpg','authors/winston-churchill','Winston Churchill','Sir Winston Churchill was born into an aristocratic family and held government positions for the majority of his adult life. Churchill served during WWI as First Lord of the Admiralty. After the war, the conservative Churchill served as Chancellor of the Exchequer. During WWII, Churchill again served as First Lord of the Admiralty, until he became Prime Minister after Neville Chamberlain resigned in 1940. As PM, Churchill was noted for his wartime radio broadcasts and speeches, which helped rally the national spirit, and his active opposition to Hitler helped secure Allied victory over Nazi Germany. The Conservative Party lost the 1945 election, but after winning the 1951 election, Churchill became Prime Minister again before retiring in 1955.'),
    (4,'0115',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/martin-luther-king-jr.jpg','authors/martin-luther-king-jr','Martin Luther King (Jr.)','Dr. King was a Baptist minister who became a leader in the African American Civil Rights Movement early in his career. In 1954, at age 25, King became pastor of the Dexter Avenue Baptist Church in Montgomery, Alabama, and completed his Ph.D. in systematic theology the following year. He led the 1955 Montgomery Bus Boycott and helped found and became the president of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference. King organized nonviolent protests against African American segregation in Birmingham, Alabama as well as the 1963 March on Washington, where he gave his famous “I Have a Dream” speech. King received the 1964 Nobel Peace Prize for his combating racial inequality through nonviolence and was assassinated by James Earl Ray four years later, at age 39.'),
    (5,'',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/confucius.jpg','authors/confucius','Confucius','Confucius was born in 551 BC in Zou, Lu State (present-day Qufu, Shandong Province, China). His father was a military officer who died when he was three years old, so he was raised by his mother in poverty. He belonged to the shi class, which was between the common people and the aristocracy. Confucius began a political career, rising to Minister of Crime of Lu State. However, he made powerful enemies and had to leave the state in exile. He then traveled throughout China sharing his philosophical and political beliefs. Confucius is traditionally credited with writing numerous Chinese classic texts and aphorisms, many of which were compiled in the Analects after his death.'),
    (6,'0730',1,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/cyril-northcote-parkinson','Cyril Northcote Parkinson','Cyril Northcote Parkinson was born in England in 1909. While attending St. Peter’s School, York, Parkinson won a scholarship to the University of Cambridge, receiving his BA in 1932. Parkinson attended graduate school at King’s College London, and his Ph.D. thesis received the 1935 Julian Corbett Prize in Naval History. Throughout his career, Parkinson held a number of teaching positions and published 60 books that distinguished him as an important scholar of naval history and public administration. His most famous book was Parkinson’s Law (1958), a collection of satirical essays about the inevitability of bureaucratic expansion.<br />\n'),
    (7,'0512',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/09/george-carlin.jpg','authors/george-carlin','George Carlin','George Carlin was born in Manhattan in 1937. Carlin attended Catholic schools and excelled in drama. As a young man, Carlin joined the U.S. Air Force and also worked as a disc jockey in Louisiana and Texas. He started working as a comedian in 1959, performing at a coffeehouse in Fort Worth, Texas. In the 1960s, Carlin began appearing regularly on TV variety shows such as The Ed Sullivan Show and The Tonight Show. Carlin recorded his first of 14 HBO comedy specials in 1977, with his routines focusing on criticizing modern American culture from the late-1980s on. Carlin died of heart failure, at 71 years old, in 2008.\n'),
    (8,'0712',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/henry-david-thoreau.jpg','authors/henry-david-thoreau','Henry David Thoreau','Henry David Thoreau, born David Henry Thoreau, was born into a modest New England family in Concord, Mass. Thoreau went to Harvard, studying rhetoric and philosophy, though he reportedly refused to pay the five-dollar fee for a Harvard diploma. After graduation, Thoreau moved back to Concord, where he met transcendentalist writer Ralph Waldo Emerson, who encouraged Thoreau to publish his essays and poems. In 1845, Thoreau embarked on a two-year experiment in “simple living,” moving into a small cabin owned by Emerson at Walden Pond. It was here where he would write his most influential work, Walden. Thoreau would also become known for his political essay Civil Disobedience. The writer died in 1862 at age 44 of tuberculosis.'),
    (9,'1028',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/09/bill-gates.jpg','authors/bill-gates','Bill Gates','Bill Gates was born in Seattle, Washington in 1955. He attended an exclusive prep school and started writing computer programs as a young teen. At 17, he formed his first company, Traf-O-Data. Gates attended Harvard, where he continued to advance his programming skills, eventually dropping out to form Microsoft. Along with other pioneers like Apple/Steve Jobs, Microsoft would start the personal computer revolution, and Gates would become one of the richest men in the world. At Microsoft, Gates held the positions of CEO and chief software architect, and is the company’s largest individual shareholder. Today, Gates works full-time for the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation, while remaining at Microsoft as chairman.\n'),
    (10,'0525',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/ralph-waldo-emerson.jpg','authors/ralph-waldo-emerson','Ralph Waldo Emerson','Boston-born Ralph Waldo Emerson was not an exceptional student at Harvard, but upon graduation, he began developing his own unique writing style as an essayist and poet. Emerson eventually became a leading figure in Transcendentalism, a movement that championed individualism and whose ideas were disseminated in Emerson’s groundbreaking 1836 essay, Nature. Emerson went on to publish several collections of essays, poems, and lectures, including his most notable Essays: First Series and Essays: Second Series. Many of Emerson’s essays were originally written as lectures and later revised for print. Emerson was married twice (his first wife, Ellen Louisa Tucker, died of tuberculosis at age 20) and was best friends with fellow Transcendentalist writer Henry David Thoreau.'),
    (11,'',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/aristotle.jpg','authors/aristotle','Aristotle','Born in Stagiros in northern Greece, he attended the Academy of Plato. After Plato’s death in 347, Aristotle became a wanderer, and in 342 took a position as tutor to Alexander, son of King Philip of Macedon. As a philosopher and natural scientist, Aristotle is considered one of the most important figures in history, and was probably the last person who could have known the sum total of his culture’s knowledge. A prolific writer, he originated the breaking down of knowledge into separate fields and wrote on almost all of them. After Alexander took the Macedonian throne, Aristotle retired to Athens and later Euboea, where he died.'),
    (12,'0224',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/steve-jobs.jpg','authors/steve-jobs','Steve Jobs','Steve Jobs was one of the most important figures in the computer revolution that began in the late twentieth century. He was born to a couple of college students, and adopted soon after. Jobs was a bright child, the school recommended he skip two grades, though he only skipped one, but not a particularly good student. While in high school, Jobs met Steve Wozniak, with whom he would later found Apple. Jobs went to college for six months, before dropping out. He worked briefly for Atari, before spending seven months in India and then returning to Atari. In 1976, he co-founded Apple with Wozniak. Jobs stayed with Apple until he was forced out in1985, and went on to found NeXT. Apple bought NeXT in 1996, bringing Jobs back to the company. Jobs quickly became the driving force behind Apple and remained involved with the company until his death from pancreatic cancer in 2011.'),
    (13,'0718',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/nelson-mandela.jpg','authors/nelson-mandela','Nelson Mandela','Nelson Mandela was born to the Thembu royal family in South Africa in 1918. Attending university in Johannesburg, he studied law and became involved in anti-colonial politics. As a young lawyer, Mandela became involved in the African National Congress party, speaking out against the policy of apartheid. In 1962, Mandela was convicted of sabotage and conspiracy to overthrow the government and was sentenced to life in prison. He served 27 years and upon his release, helped abolish apartheid and establish multi-racial elections. In the 1994 general election, Mandela was elected President of South Africa. In his retirement, Mandela has continued his activism and focused on combating HIV/AIDS and other causes through the Nelson Mandela Foundation.'),
    (14,'',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/lao-tzu1.jpg','authors/lao-tzu','Lao Tzu','Lao Tzu, the founder of Taoism, was born in 6th-century BCE China. As a philosopher, he attracted a large number of disciples, though he never opened an official school. Not much is known about Lao Tzu’s biography with certainty, but according to many traditional biographies, Lao Tzu was a scholar who worked as the Keeper of the Archives in the royal court of Zhou. This job was boring and gave him lots of time to think. Working for the royal court, Lao Tzu saw much corruption around him and decided to leave the country, traveling west on a water buffalo. A guard recognized him and demanded he write down his teachings. According to legend, these collected teachings became the Tao Te Ching.'),
    (15,'0721',33,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/12/robin-williams.jpg','authors/robin-williams','Robin Williams',''),
    (16,'0824',16,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/dave-chappelle','Dave Chappelle',''),
    (17,'0826',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/mother-teresa.jpg','authors/mother-teresa','Mother Teresa','Mother Teresa was born to Albanian parents in what was then the Ottoman Empire, and is now Macedonia. At the age of 18, she took holy orders and moved to India to become a nun. Once in India, she served primarily as a teacher for almost 20 years before receiving what she later termed “the call within the call,” in 1946. Leaving the school, she took up the sari and began what later became known as the Missionaries of Charity. As a missionary, she became the personification of charity in the twentieth century. She died of complications due to heart disease in September 1997 at the age of 87. She was beatified in 2003'),
    (18,'0611',31,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/vince-lombardi.jpg','authors/vince-lombardi','Vince Lombardi','The son of Italian immigrants, Vincent Thomas “Vince” Lombardi was born in Brooklyn, New York in 1913. At age 12, Lombardi started playing in an organized football league and continued to play in high school. In 1933, Lombardi accepted a scholarship to Fordham University to play for the Fordham Rams. Lombardi later coached at St. Cecilia High School,  followed by Fordham, West Point, and finally, the NFL. Lombardi started as the offensive backfield coach of the New York Giants, and later, most famously, he became the head coach of the Green Bay Packers during the 1960s. He was also the head coach of the Washington Redskins in 1969. Lombardi never had a single losing season as a head coach in the NFL.'),
    (19,'0830',40,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/07/warren-buffett.jpg','authors/warren-buffett','Warren Buffett','Warren Buffet was born in 1930 in Omaha, Nebraska, the only son of U.S. Representative Howard Buffet. As a child, Buffet showed interest in making money and even started investing in the stock market. In 1951, he earned a Master of Science in economics from Columbia and started working as an investment salesman. He went on to work as a securities analyst and stockbroker, opened various partnerships, and started making investments. By 1962, he was a millionaire. In 1990, Buffet became a billionaire as a result of his investments, including Berkshire Hathaway, of which he is the chairman, CEO, and primary shareholder. He is consistently ranked as one of the world’s wealthiest people.\n'),
    (20,'0218',32,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/yoko-ono','Yoko Ono',''),
    (21,'0627',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/helen-keller.jpg','authors/helen-keller','Helen Keller','At age 19 months, Helen Keller contracted an illness that left her death and blind. Anne Sullivan became Keller’s instructor, teaching her how to communicate using her hands. Keller attended a series of prestigious schools, including Radcliffe College. In 1904 at age 24, Keller became the first deaf-blind person to earn a Bachelor’s degree. Keller would go on to become a famous speaker and writer, publishing 12 books. She was also an advocate of various causes, including people with disabilities, women’s suffrage, pacifism, and birth control for women. Keller died in her sleep, a few weeks short of her 88th birthday.'),
    (22,'',1,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/malala-yousafzai','Malala Yousafzai',''),
    (23,'0423',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/william-shakespeare.jpg','authors/william-shakespeare','William Shakespeare','Much more is known about Shakespeare the playwright than Shakespeare the man. His birth and marriage to Anne Hathaway in 1582 are known, as are the births of his three children, Susanna in 1583 and the twins Hamnet and Judith in 1585. From that point, he vanishes until 1592, by which point he was already known in the London theatrical scene. As a partner in the Lord Chamberlains, and later the King’s, Men, he was a successful actor and playwright and became a wealthy man. By 1606 he had largely retired, and completely by 1613. His work remains his true epitaph.\n'),
    (24,'0129',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/02/oprah-winfrey.jpg','authors/oprah-winfrey','Oprah Winfrey','Oprah Winfrey was born to an impoverished teenage mother in rural Mississippi and later raised in inner-city Milwaukee. Winfrey was raped at age 9 and became pregnant at 14. After being sent to live with the man she refers to as her father in Tennessee, Winfrey started working at a radio station in high school and was co-anchoring the local evening news by age 19. In 1983, she relocated to Chicago to host the morning talk show AM Chicago. Ratings for the show soared and it was renamed The Oprah Winfrey Show and broadcast nationally. The show would become the highest-rated talk show in history. Today, Oprah is one of the richest and most influential African Americans, and women, in the world.'),
    (25,'',48,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/buddha.jpg','authors/buddha','Buddha','According to most traditional biographies, the Buddha was a prince born into a royal Hindu family. His family tried to shield him from suffering, but at age 29, the Buddha left his palace and encountered a sick person, an old person, a corpse, and an ascetic. Buddha decided to avow his princely life and become an ascetic. However, according to the legend, he did not reach enlightenment until meditating at the Bodhi tree for 49 days. Upon awakening, the Buddha realized the cause of suffering and the way out of it, insights which he would spend the rest of his life teaching and which would form the basis of the Buddhist religion.'),
    (26,'0117',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/benjamin-franklin.jpg','authors/benjamin-franklin','Benjamin Franklin','Born to colonial parents of modest means, Benjamin Franklin’s formal schooling ended at age 10. He became an apprentice to his brother, a printer, at age 12. At age 17, he ran away to Philadelphia, working as a typesetter. In 1728, Franklin set up his own printing house and newspaper, The Pennsylvania Gazette, and in 1733, he began to publish the popular pamphlet Poor Richard’s Almanack. Aside from publishing, Franklin was also quite involved with public affairs and his work as a scientist and inventor. During the American Revolution, Franklin campaigned for colonial unity and helped draft the Declaration of Independence. Some other hats Franklin wore included first U.S. Postmaster General, first U.S. Ambassador to France, and President of Pennsylvania.'),
    (27,'0314',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/02/albert-einstein.jpg','authors/albert-einstein','Albert Einstein','Albert Einstein was a theoretical physicist who revolutionized the world of physics with his general and special theories of relativity. Pivotal to these theories was Einstein’s most famous equation, the mass-energy equivalence formula (E = mc2). Born in Germany, Einstein settled in the U.S. after Adolf Hitler came to power in 1933, continuing the impressive academic and scientific career he had established in Europe. Throughout his long career, Einstein published hundreds of books and articles. Einstein’s warnings to President Franklin D. Roosevelt that Germany might be creating a nuclear weapon were instrumental to the United States’ development of the atomic bomb. He died at age 76 of a ruptured abdominal aortic aneurysm.'),
    (28,'',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/plato.jpg','authors/plato','Plato','Plato was born to an aristocratic family in 400s BC Greece. As a boy, he was instructed in grammar, philosophy, and gymnastics. Plato became a follower of the philosopher Socrates and helped him write the Socratic dialogues, which laid the foundations for Western philosophy. Plato considered a career in politics, but after Socrates’ trial and execution, Plato soured to the idea and began traveling extensively. During his travels, Plato produced such works as The Republic. Upon his return to Athens, Plato established one of the earliest known schools in the Western world, the Academy, which he would preside over until his death. One of Plato’s most promising students there was Aristotle, to whom he would become a mentor.'),
    (29,'0125',4,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/gloria-naylor','Gloria Naylor',''),
    (30,'0404',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/maya-angelou.jpg','authors/maya-angelou','Maya Angelou','Maya Angelou had a turbulent childhood, living with various relatives and being sexually abused by her mother’s boyfriend at age eight. Angelou’s early life was documented in her 1969 novel, I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings, which brought her international acclaim as a writer. Prior to publishing Caged Bird, Angelou worked as a successful dancer, singer, and civil rights activist, serving as the Northern Organizer for Martin Luther King, Jr.’s Southern Christian Leadership Conference. In her career as a writer, Angelou has published seven autobiographies, as well as plays, screenplays, and many volumes of poetry. Angelou has also had a successful career as an actor, narrator, and lecturer.'),
    (31,'1016',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/oscar-wilde.jpg','authors/oscar-wilde','Oscar Wilde','Oscar Wilde was born to Anglo-Irish intellectuals, becoming fluent in German and French at a young age. He read the Greats at university and became involved in the aestheticism movement, returning to London after graduation to work as a journalist. He became a well-known personality and writer in London, parlaying his ideas about art and society into essays, plays, and his only novel, The Picture of Dorian Gray. At the height of his success, Wilde was prosecuted for homosexual activities and was imprisoned in a hard labor camp for two years. Upon his release, and in poor health, Wilde went to Paris, where he died at age 46.'),
    (32,'1129',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/c-s-lewis.jpg','authors/c-s-lewis','C. S. Lewis','Clive Staples Lewis was born and grew up in Belfast, Ireland. As a boy, he was fascinated by animals and books. Lewis was awarded a scholarship to Oxford, where he studied English, Philosophy, and Ancient Studies. He was elected a Fellow and Tutor in English Literature at Magdalen College, Oxford, and served there for 29 years. While an English professor at Oxford, Lewis wrote a number of books, including the wildly successful Chronicles of Narnia books and other fiction, academic works, and nonfiction Christian books. Lewis died of renal failure at age 65, though his death was overshadowed by that of JFK, which occurred on the same day.'),
    (33,'1011',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/eleanor-roosevelt.jpg','authors/eleanor-roosevelt','Eleanor Roosevelt','Despite being born into a rich and prominent family, Anna Eleanor Roosevelt suffered an unhappy childhood after her parents and brother died at a young age. In 1905, after attending university in London, she returned to the U.S. and married her sixth cousin, Franklin D. Roosevelt, with whom she would have six children. After Eleanor’s husband contracted polio and became a paraplegic in 1921, she encouraged him to stay in politics, and he later became president in 1932. Eleanor was also active in politics, becoming one of the United Nations’ first delegates and chairing JFK’s Presidential Commission on the Status of Women. Roosevelt was the longest-serving First Lady and arguably the most influential.'),
    (34,'1205',42,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/walt-disney.jpg','authors/walt-disney','Walt Disney','Walt Disney was born in Chicago in 1901, to an Irish-Canadian family that could trace its ancestry back to the Norman Conquest. As a young man, he tried to enlist in the army but was too young, though he eventually went to France as a Red Cross Ambulance driver after the war ended. Back in the US, hee returned to Kansas City where he started an animation studio with Ubbe Iwerks. After losing the character Oswald the Lucky Rabbit to Universal, Disney rebounded with Mickey Mouse in Steamboat Willie, a character and film that laid the foundation for all that followed. By 1950 Disney expanded to live-action, and by Disneyland which opened in 1955. Disney himself died of lung cancer in 1966, just after his 65th birthday.'),
    (35,'',8,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/lydia-maria-child','Lydia Maria Child',''),
    (36,'0108',43,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/stephen-hawking.jpg','authors/stephen-hawking','Stephen Hawking','Stephen William Hawking was born in Oxford, during the Second World War. His family lived in London, but left the city temporarily because of the bombing. After school, Hawking went to Oxford, but did not excel despite his intelligence. He did obtain the First Class Honours he needed to go to Cambridge, but was also diagnosed with motor neuron disease in 1963 and given a two year life expectancy. Initially depressed, he recovered his enthusiasm and earned his doctorate in 1966. Even as his physical health declined, Hawking’s mental abilities remained sharp.  He shot up in the public eye after his 1988 book A Brief History of Time. Hawking married and divorced twice. As his body failed Hawking lost not only the ability to walk and move his limbs, but also the power of speech, necessitating the development of computer assisted communications systems for him.  He has come to represent both genius and the ability to overcome physical handicaps to millions.'),
    (37,'',1,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/steve-moris','Steve Moris',''),
    (38,'1130',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/02/mark-twain.jpg','authors/mark-twain','Mark Twain','Samuel Clemens, a.k.a. Mark Twain, grew up in Hannibal, Missouri, which would later provide the setting for his books The Adventures of Tom Sawyer and Adventures of Huckleberry Finn. He started contributing humorous sketches and articles to the newspaper his brother owned, the Hannibal Journal, at age 12. At 18, Twain moved to New York, working as a printer. He later became a riverboat pilot on the Mississippi River an also spent some time in the American West as a miner. While Twain’s major published works were his abovementioned classic novels, he also published many essays, sketches, stories, literary reviews, and travelogue pieces. Later in life, Twain was awarded honorary degrees from Yale, Oxford, and the University of Missouri.'),
    (39,'0706',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/dalai-lama.jpg','authors/dalai-lama','Dalai Lama','The 14th Dalai Lama was selected as the rebirth of the 13th Dalai Lama two years after his birth in 1935, though he was only formally recognized as the 14th Dalai Lama in 1950 when he was 15. During the 1959 Tibetan uprising, the Dalai Lama fled to India, where he established a Tibetan government in exile and denounced the People’s Republic of China. Since then, he has traveled the world, advocating for the welfare of Tibetans and teaching the principles of Tibetan Buddhism. In 1989, the Dalai Lama won the Nobel Peace Prize. The 14th Dalai Lama is the longest-living Dalai Lama.'),
    (40,'0629',1,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/harmon-killebrew','Harmon Killebrew',''),
    (41,'0212',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/02/abraham-lincoln.jpg','authors/abraham-lincoln','Abraham Lincoln','Born in a one-room log cabin in Kentucky, Abraham Lincoln rose to become the 16th President of the United States. He was a lawyer and politician, noted for his anti-slavery views. In the 1850s, as the influence of the slave states on the federal government grew stronger, Lincoln returned to politics, winning the 1860 Presidential election entirely on the strength of the free states. The South seceded shortly thereafter, plunging the US into the Civil War. Lincoln ran the country throughout the war, signing the Emancipation Act in 1862. As the war ended, he was Assassinated by John Wilkes Booth at the Ford Theater in Washington DC.'),
    (42,'0531',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/walt-whitman.jpg','authors/walt-whitman','Walt Whitman','Born to a poor family on Long Island, Walt Whitman left school at 11 to work to help support his family by working at a printer. He tried several jobs, including both teaching and editing as well as other jobs in the print industry. By 1850 he had begun what became his life’s work, the poetry collection Leaves of Grass, which he would work on throughout his life. He self-published the first edition in 1855, and continued to publish revised editions throughout his life. The earthy nature of his poetry affected his reputation and made it hard for him to keep a job. He suffered a stroke in 1873, becoming an invalid for the rest of his life. He died in 1892 of complications and pleurisy.'),
    (43,'',1,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/photo-unavailable.jpg','authors/fields-wicker-miurin','Fields Wicker-Miurin',''),
    (44,'0405',31,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/bette-davis.jpg','authors/bette-davis','Bette Davis','Ruth Elizabeth Davis was known from early childhood as “Betty.” As a teen, Davis was inspired to become an actress and changed her name’s spelling to “Bette.” Davis starred in two Broadway plays in the 1920s and traveled to Hollywood in 1930. In the 1930s and early ’40s, Davis was one of Hollywood’s leading ladies, starting in dozens of films, including the critically acclaimed Of Human Bondage (1934) and Dangerous (1935). After some professional setbacks in the ‘40s and ‘50s, Davis experienced renewed success after starring in What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? in 1962. That same year, Davis became the first person to receive ten Oscar nominations for acting. Davis died in 1989 at age 81.'),
    (45,'1207',7,0,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/04/jason-bacchetta.jpg','authors/jason-bacchetta','Jason Bacchetta','Jason Bacchetta is a serial entrepreneur, the founder of DIGIQ Media, as well as the founder of Quotery.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
    (46,'0117',1,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/09/al-capone.jpg','authors/al-capone','Al Capone','Alphonse Gabriel “Al” Capone was born to a family of Italian immigrants in Brooklyn, New York in 1899. After being expelled from school at age 14, Capone became involved in gang activity. During Prohibition, Capone moved to Chicago to smuggle alcohol into the city. Capone’s reputation as a “modern-day Robin Hood” was damaged by his involvement in the 1929 Saint Valentine’s Day Massacre. In 1931, Capone was sentenced to federal prison after being convicted for tax evasion. In his final years, Capone was afflicted by the physical and mental effects of late-stage neuro-syphilis. He died in 1947, at age 48, from cardiac arrest following a stroke.\n'),
    (47,'0612',29,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/anne-frank.jpg','authors/anne-frank','Anne Frank','As a young child, Annelies “Anne” Marie Frank moved with her family, which was of Jewish descent, from Germany to Amsterdam in 1933 after the Nazis gained control over Germany. In school, Anne excelled in reading and writing. By 1940, the Nazis had also occupied the Netherlands, and in 1942, as prosecutions of Jews increased, the Franks went into hiding in some hidden rooms in the building where Anne’s father, Otto, worked. While in hiding, Anne kept a diary of her experiences that would later be published as The Diary of a Young Girl. In 1944, the family was betrayed and sent to concentration camps. Anne and her sister Margot died of typhus in the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp in 1945.'),
    (48,'0601',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/09/marilyn-monroe.jpg','authors/marilyn-monroe','Marilyn Monroe','Marilyn Monroe was born in Los Angeles, California, in 1926. Monroe (born Norma Jeane Mortenson) grew up mostly in foster homes. She started a career as a model and then landed a film contract with Twentieth Century Fox in 1946, appearing in films such as All About Eve (1950), Niagra (1953), and The Seven Year Itch (1955). Monroe broadened her range by studying at Actors Studio, leading to critically acclaimed performances in films such as Bus Stop (1956) and Some Like It Hot (1959). Monroe died in 1962 at age 36 after overdosing on barbiturates. Today, she remains a cultural icon and American sex symbol.\n'),
    (49,'0429',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/09/jerry-seinfeld.jpg','authors/jerry-seinfeld','Jerry Seinfeld','Jerry Seinfeld was born in Brooklyn, New York in 1954. He developed an interest in standup comedy in college and an open-mic night performance led to an appearance in a Rodney Dangerfield HBO special. In 1979, Seinfeld had a small recurring role on the TV series Benson, and he soon started appearing regularly on The Tonight Show and other shows. Seinfeld, the TV series Seinfeld co-created with Larry David, debuted in 1989. By its fourth season, Seinfeld had become the most popular show on TV. Since Seinfeld ended in 1998, Seinfeld has returned to stand-up comedy and has made various TV and movie appearances.\n'),
    (50,'0731',50,1,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/06/j-k-rowling.jpg','authors/j-k-rowling','J. K. Rowling','J.K. Rowling, born Joanne Rowling, was on a long train trip, working as a secretary  for Amnesty International when she first conceived of the idea for her Harry Potter series, which would go on to become the best-selling book series of all time. Rowling was surviving on state benefits when she completed Harry Potter and the Sorcerer’s Stone. Although she was advised not to quit her day job after the British publishing house Bloomsbury agreed to publish the book in 1997, Harry Potter would become a global brand worth $15 billion. Rowling is now among the richest women in England and is also an active philanthropist.\n');
INSERT INTO `collection` VALUES
    (1,37,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2016/06/winston-churchill-memorial.jpg','collections/fascinating-winston-churchill-quotes','Fascinating Winston Churchill Quotes','Many know Winston Churchill as the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom; a man who played a large role in leading the Allies to victory in WWII. But he also happened to be a terrific speaker, a big fan of reading books of quotations, and an excellent writer–eventually being awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature.\r\n\r\nWith a resume like that, it isn\'t hard to imagine that Winston Churchill had quite a few quips that are still frequently quoted today. Indeed, many of Churchill\'s words are inspiring and funny, but in this list of 42 fascinating Winston Churchill quotes, you might be surprised to find out that he also had a dark side that most would call racist. Read on and decide for yourself.'),
    (2,23,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/06/father-and-son.jpg','collections/remarkable-fathers-day-quotes','Remarkable Father\'s Day Quotes','Recently, we published a list of 23 Wonderful Mother\'s Day Quotes, but let\'s not forget that it took two to bring you into this world. Father\'s Day is another occasion that is just as prominent in most countries. In fact, Father\'s Day was first observed in 1908, just two months after Mother\'s Day was first celebrated.\r\n\r\nFathers — both biological fathers and those special people who take on this role in your life voluntarily — deserve to be praised and appreciated for all they do for us. They are often the source of strength in our families growing up: our dads are both our protectors and the ones who work hard to support the family, with minimal complaints.\r\n\r\nEnjoy these 23 remarkable Father\'s Day quotes, and hand-pick one or two favorites to include in your Father\'s Day card to Dad this year for a personal touch.'),
    (3,39,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/04/athlete-on-track.jpg','collections/motivational-fitness-quotes-get-shape','Motivational Fitness Quotes (To Get In Shape)','Fitness, exercise, and healthy habits overall can have a major impact on how we live the rest of our lives. We all know that. Yet, too many of us find ourselves lacking motivation to get off the couch. We skip the gym, replace outdoor activities with television and computers, and use technology to become lazier whenever the opportunity presents itself.\r\n\r\nWhy? Because it\'s easier, and the consequences aren\'t immediately recognized.\r\n\r\nFortunately, sometimes we just need a little push . . . a reminder . . . a few words of wisdom. And quotes just happen to be our expertise. Read on to take advantage of these 40 motivational quotes that\'ll hopefully inspire you to get in shape.'),
    (4,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2016/06/corrupt-politician-swearing-an-oath.jpg','collections/political-election-day-quotes','Political Election Day Quotes','If you have mixed feelings about Election Day, you\'re not alone. While most citizens do cherish their individual right to vote, they often find themselves disappointed with the candidates and the results. We all have a difference of opinions, and our public officials are far from perfect, but few would rather live in a society supported by anything other than democracy.\r\n\r\nIn preparation for another year of intense debates, here are 130 political Election Day quotes from presidents, philosophers, comedians, and everyday taxpayers.'),
    (5,45,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2018/09/thanskgiving-day-dinner.jpg','collections/festive-thanksgiving-quotes-celebrating-gratitude','Festive Thanksgiving Quotes Celebrating Gratitude','Every year on the fourth Thursday of November, Americans get together with family and friends to give thanks for the blessings they have in life. In many households, these celebrations involve plenty of feasting, football, and even late-night shopping.\r\n\r\nTo kick-off the start of the holiday season and the ensuing chaos, here are 45 festive Thanksgiving quotes celebrating gratitude.'),
    (6,19,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2016/06/photo-of-steve-jobs-displayed-on-an-apple-ipad.jpg','collections/innovative-quotes-steve-jobs','Innovative Quotes From Steve Jobs','Steve Jobs was one of the greatest inventors of our time; playing a major role in transforming the way we interact with computers, smartphones, movies, music, and apps. It doesn\'t take a fan of Apple (which Job’s co-founded) products to realize that the company\'s innovation has benefited all of us as consumers.\r\n\r\nIf you\'ve ever wondered what thoughts drive a billionaire entrepreneur to success, perhaps these 20 innovative quotes from Steve Jobs will provide some insight.'),
    (7,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/05/boy-laughing.jpg','collections/humorous-quotes-amusement','More Humorous Quotes for Your Amusement','What is it, exactly, that makes a quote or statement funny? It\'s hard to define, but funny quotes often make us laugh by saying something that is unexpected or exaggerated, but still has a ring of truth to it. Good joke subjects include edgy topics like sex or drunkenness, situations or people that annoy us, like in-laws or politicians, and even political topics.\r\n\r\nEssentially, anything that allows us to laugh at other people, at a common life occurrence, or even at ourselves can be great comedic material. There\'s all different kinds of humor, and this list of humorous quotes has all of them, from plays-on-words, to clever insults, to humorous observations.\r\n\r\nIf you haven\'t already, be sure to also check out the first installment of humorous quotes: 100 Funny Quotes Worth Laughing Over.'),
    (8,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/05/writer-at-work.jpg','collections/enlightening-quotes-aspiring-writers','Enlightening Quotes for Aspiring Writers','Being an exceptional writer isn\'t easy. It requires discipline, patience, creativity, a good command of the English language, and in many cases... the willingness to work for little pay (or, no pay at all).\r\n\r\nBut that doesn\'t mean it can\'t be done. As is the case with every other profession, nobody starts off as an expert, and not everyone does it for money. For many, writing is a pleasure and a passion.\r\n\r\nLuckily, it just so happens that there have been quite a few successful writers that have come before us. It\'s their wisdom that has inspired this article; a list of 125 enlightening quotes for aspiring writers.'),
    (9,29,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/10/halloween-pumpkins-on-fence.jpg','collections/wickedly-wonderful-halloween-quotes','Wickedly Wonderful Halloween Quotes','It\'s officially October and chances are you\'re starting to see the Halloween decorations come out. It\'s the only time of year when neighbors proudly display pumpkins, skeletons, tombstones, spiders and cobwebs.\r\n\r\nIn other words, now\'s the time to start picking out your spooky costumes, creepy music, and of course, a scary quote or two.\r\n\r\nHappy Halloween!'),
    (10,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/05/friends-having-fun.jpg','collections/uplifting-friendship-quotes','Uplifting Friendship Quotes','Friendship quotes remind us that a true friend is irreplaceable. Friends laugh with us in times of prosperity, console us through adversity, and are always willing to offer advice when needed.\r\n\r\nThey\'re known as many things. Our companions and comrades. Our sidekicks and our buddies. We have new friends, best friends, and \"old friends\". But regardless of what title we give them, one thing is certain: they are a wonderful thing to have in this life.\r\n\r\nTo capture the essence of good friends, below we present 60 uplifting friendship quotes that\'ll have you feeling appreciative and blessed.'),
    (11,23,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/05/dr-seuss-quotes.jpg','collections/memorable-dr-seuss-quotes','Memorable Dr. Seuss Quotes','Theodore Seuss Geisel, better known by his pen name of Dr. Seuss, is one of the most beloved children\'s authors of all time; for many people, a Dr. Seuss book like Green Eggs and Ham or Hop on Pop was the first book they ever learned how to read. Using humorous rhymes, delightful illustrations, and a wild imagination, Dr. Seuss was perhaps the first author to make reading fun, both for kids and for their parents and teachers.\r\n\r\nDr. Seuss\'s books also teach important lessons, such as the importance of treating everyone equally, the benefits of being open-minded, and the amazing things you can achieve if you believe in yourself. What\'s more, unbeknownst to the children who read them, many of Dr. Seuss\'s books were actually subtle satires of political events. Learn the fascinating back-stories of 25 memorable Dr. Seuss quotes.'),
    (12,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/03/field-of-freedom.jpg','collections/top-inspirational-quotes-all-time','Top 50 Inspirational Quotes of All Time','Inspirational quotes are perfect for those who are looking for motivation, encouragement, and positivity in their lives. Just a few words of wisdom can inspire you to succeed, galvanize your ambitions, and embolden you to take action.\r\n\r\nEnlightening quotes have many applications. Professional speakers use them to deliver effective and powerful messages. Life coaches use them to invigorate their students. And team leaders utilize quotations to empower their coworkers. Of course, many of us also have our own personal collection of inspirational quotes, and sharing them with friends on social media is just as gratifying.\r\n\r\nIn this list of 100 inspirational quotes to lift you up, we\'ve included maxims spoken by people from all walks of life, including presidents, athletes, philosophers, and everything in between.'),
    (13,40,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/06/us-flag-fireworks-and-statue-of-liberty.jpg','collections/patriotic-independence-day-quotes','Patriotic Independence Day Quotes','July 4th is just around the corner, and — as always — we\'ve got you covered when trying to find the perfect quote for the occasion.\r\n\r\nFor Americans, the Fourth of July is a day of great pride and jubilation that we use to celebrate our history, liberty, and traditions of the United States.\r\n\r\nOf course, other countries around the world also observe their own events that represent some sort of national importance, whether it be a declaration of freedom, or the formation of a state or constitution. Independence Day, National Day, Revolution Day, and Republic Day are all commonly used terms to describe the comparable holidays.\r\n\r\nBut regardless of where the anniversary takes place, fireworks, picnics, parades, concerts, and backyard barbeques are just a few of many festivities that are commonly associated with the holiday.\r\n\r\nIn anticipation of this year\'s lively entertainment, here are 44 patriotic Independence Day quotes to get you fired up with enthusiasm.'),
    (14,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/02/newlyweds.jpg','collections/top-love-quotes-all-time','Top 50 Love Quotes of All Time','Love is often hard to describe with words alone. Fortunately, from the work of notable authors, poets, and philosophers, we were able to unearth quite a few incredible love quotes that should help you communicate your true feelings.\r\n\r\nLove is one of the most cherished ideas of Western society — after all, don\'t the majority of songs we hear, movies we watch, and books we read tell some kind of love story?\r\n\r\nIndeed, love comes in many forms: love shared between sweethearts, love you have for your friends, love for God or nature, familial love, the love you express to the world at large, and even the love you have for yourself.\r\n\r\nAnd with that comes many different ways to express your love, be it romantic, cute, cheesy, or agonizing. But don\'t worry, in this list of 100 love quotes that come from the heart, we\'ve included quotations that represent each type of love.\r\n\r\nWithout further ado...'),
    (15,22,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/05/mother-and-daughter.jpg','collections/wonderful-mothers-day-quotes','Wonderful Mother\'s Day Quotes','Mother\'s Day, which takes place on the second Sunday of May each year in the United States, has only been an official holiday for about a hundred years. However, celebrations of motherhood have been taking place for many thousands of years, among everyone from the ancient Romans to the ancient Egyptians.\r\n\r\nWhether it\'s Mother\'s Day or any other day of the year, it\'s important to let your mother know how much she means to you. Incorporating one of these 23 Wonderful Mother\'s Day Quotes into a gift or card for her is a great way to do it; a classic quote that you personally selected is a lot more thoughtful than a random Hallmark card.\r\n\r\nUse this list to find the perfect quote to celebrate the most special woman in your life.'),
    (16,24,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/03/martin-luther-king-jr.jpg','collections/inspiring-quotes-martin-luther-king','Inspiring Quotes from Martin Luther King, Jr.','Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. is an icon in American history who was instrumental in expanding the rights of African Americans through the civil rights movement of the 1950s and \'60s. The legacy of this incredibly influential civil rights leader and minister lives on through his brave actions, as well as his eloquent and inspirational words.\r\n\r\nDr. King\'s famous \"I Have a Dream\" speech is widely considered the top American speech of the 20th century, and many other inspirational words of MLK are frequently quoted due to their wisdom and continued relevance in today\'s world. Read on for some of the most inspiring Martin Luther King, Jr. quotes and their interpretations.'),
    (17,18,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2016/07/kanye-west-at-takashi-murakami-exhibition.jpg','collections/outrageously-arrogant-quotes-kanye-west','Outrageously Arrogant Quotes From Kanye West','Kanye West, the American rapper and entrepreneur, is definitely no stranger to controversy. In fact, you might even say he genuinely enjoys it. After all, as William Hazlitt once said, \"When a thing ceases to be a subject of controversy, it ceases to be a subject of interest.\"\r\n\r\nAt which point does confidence and having self-esteem become arrogance and narcissism? Well, that\'s debatable, but perhaps it comes at the exact moment when someone refers to himself as \"a god.\" For your entertainment, here are 18 outrageously arrogant quotes from Kanye West.'),
    (18,22,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/03/mister-rogers-wax-figure.jpg','collections/incredibly-profound-quotes-mister-rogers','Incredibly Profound Quotes From Mister Rogers','When you think of Fred Rogers–the man behind the American children\'s television series, Mister Rogers\' Neighborhood–one of the first things that likely comes to mind is a friendly face (OK, that and a cardigan sweater).\r\n\r\nMany of us know Mister Rogers as a television host. But what you may not realize is that he was much more than a character on a show. Mr. Rogers was an educator, minister, author, and a masterful source of wisdom, kindness, and inspiration.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate his birthday on March 20th (he would be 86 this year), we put together this list of 22 Incredibly Profound Quotes From Mister Rogers.'),
    (19,8,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/03/albert-einstein.jpg','collections/remarkable-albert-einstein-quotes','Remarkable Albert Einstein Quotes','Albert Einstein is one of the most frequently quoted individuals of all-time. While possessing a brilliant mind that enabled him to make groundbreaking scientific discoveries in the realm of physics, including the general and specific theories of relativity, Einstein was more than just a great scientist. He was also a personable, thoughtful man who had a keen way with words. As a result, Einstein became a sage of the modern era, a legend who people love to quote.\r\n\r\nThe following Einstein quotes are some of his most remarkable – for their wisdom, wit, irony, and impact on the world, as well as for the surprising things they reveal about this oft-misunderstood genius.'),
    (20,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/10/magic-books.jpg','collections/top-greatest-quotes-all-time','Top 50 Greatest Quotes Of All Time','As Abraham Lincoln once said, \"It is a pleasure to be able to quote lines to fit any occasion.\" We couldn\'t agree more with the former president, which is why we\'ve decided to put together this list of the top 500 greatest quotes of all time.\r\n\r\nThis list is filled with words of wisdom and entertaining quips, all of which are easily digested and recalled. Some of them have historical significance, while others are noted for their familiarity, wit, or capacity to intrigue one\'s mind.\r\n\r\nFrom Jay-Z to Robert Frost, Maya Angelou, and Abraham Lincoln; everyone was eligible for our list of famous quotes. And since everyone could use a shot of inspiration, a good laugh, and a lot of love, all topics are represented.\r\n\r\nThere are, however, a few requirements necessary for the enjoyment of this list: an open mind, a sense of humor, and the knowledge that \"Almost every wise saying has an opposite one, no less wise, to balance it.\" - George Santayana. Also keep in mind that many variations of quotes exist, and each variation is often attributed to a different author.\r\n\r\nEnjoy!'),
    (21,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/02/successful-entrepreneurs.jpg','collections/empowering-startup-quotes-successful-entrepreneurs','Empowering Startup Quotes From Successful Entrepreneurs','What is an entrepreneur? While the definition varies somewhat depending on who you ask, most would agree that an entrepreneur is someone who founds a brand-new business, or startup, taking on some degree of financial risk in order to get their company off the ground. In other words, you\'re not necessarily an entrepreneur if you rise to eminence in an established company or if you fund your startup entirely with someone else\'s money. It takes a special type of person to be an entrepreneur, because it requires you to be brave, independent, and perhaps just a little bit crazy.\r\n\r\nAre you an aspiring entrepreneur? Get inspired with these 100 empowering startup quotes from successful entrepreneurs, ranging from Thomas Edison to Steve Jobs.'),
    (22,25,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/05/american-flag.jpg','collections/glorious-memorial-day-quotes','Glorious Memorial Day Quotes','To many, Memorial Day, the federal U.S. holiday that takes place every year on the last Monday of May, is just another excuse for a three-day weekend. It\'s also known as the day that marks the official start of summer and as a day devoted to getting great deals at the mall. However, the true meaning of Memorial Day goes far beyond barbecues and mattress sales.\r\n\r\nThe holiday began after the Civil War, and at that time was known as \"Decoration Day.\" While it was originally founded to honor the soldiers who died in the Civil War, today, Memorial Day is a day to honor all of the Americans who have died in military service.\r\n\r\nPatriotic Americans should take a moment from their day of celebration and leisure to reflect on the brave sacrifices of those who have given their lives for this great nation. Get inspired by the following 25 Glorious Memorial Day Quotes, which celebrate American heroes, as well as the values that make this country worth fighting for.\r\n\r\nOh, and, don\'t forget to check out 24 Triumphant Veterans Day Quotes for even more inspiration!'),
    (23,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/05/graduation-scroll-and-mortarboard.jpg','collections/encouraging-graduation-quotes','Encouraging Graduation Quotes','Whether it\'s kindergarten, high school, or college... graduation is an exciting time for everyone involved. For students, it\'s a step closer to achieving dreams and discovering new opportunities. For family and teachers, it\'s a bittersweet moment of elation, excitement and satisfaction.\r\n\r\nTo help celebrate the occasion, here are 110 encouraging graduation quotes; perfect for cards, commencement speeches, and words of wisdom.'),
    (24,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/03/mother-teresa.jpg','collections/great-quotes-great-women','Great Quotes from Great Women','If you\'re looking for inspiring and hilarious quotes from female authors, comedians, actresses, activists, politicians, entrepreneurs and other powerful women, you\'ve come to the right place. This collection includes everything from motivational quotes from the likes of Helen Keller, Maya Angelou, Rosa Parks, Mother Theresa, and Anne Frank, to sidesplitting one-liners from Joan Rivers, Erma Bombeck, and Carol Burnett.\r\n\r\nCheck out our list of 88 Great Quotes from Great Women for wisdom, comfort, and laughs from your favorite female writers and historical figures.'),
    (25,30,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2018/03/investment-money.jpg','collections/invaluable-investment-quotes','Invaluable Investment Quotes','Whether you\'re investing in traditional stocks or up-and-coming cryptocurrencies, market cycles, the psychology of human behavior, and other common variables should factor into your decisions when choosing when and where to invest your money.\r\n\r\nBut rather than take our advice (we aren\'t financial advisors, after all), check out what some of the most successful investors on Earth have to say about what their experiences have taught them.\r\n\r\nThese quotes about investing are invaluable, but also dead-simple, allowing all of us to benefit regardless of background or know-how.'),
    (26,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2015/06/game-of-thrones-iron-throne.jpg','collections/game-thrones-quotes','\'Game of Thrones\' Quotes That\'ll Have You Begging For More','Game of Thrones — HBO\'s record-setting television series that has an average gross audience of 18.6 million viewers — certainly doesn\'t fall short when it comes to the inclusion of brilliant quotations. In fact, in creating this massive list of \'Game of Thrones\' quotes, we were only able to feature a fraction of our favorites.\r\n\r\nBe warned, some of these quotes — much like the show itself — are far from PG-13. We\'ve included funny quotes, quotes about love, and inspirational quotes. They are, at times, inappropriate, mostly insightful, and almost always powerful.\r\n\r\nSo Game of Thrones enthusiasts, go ahead and rejoice. Below, we present 77 \'Game of Thrones\' quotes that\'ll have you begging for more.'),
    (27,14,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2018/02/coffee-beans.jpg','collections/delightful-coffee-quotes','Delightful Coffee Quotes','For many of us, coffee is our morning savior. It\'s the motivation to get out of bed. It masks our lack of enthusiasm for seizing the day. And it allows us to taste the satisfaction of productivity.\r\n\r\nOne cup is rarely, if ever, enough — as demonstrated by  the 25 million bags of coffee imported annually by the United States.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate our delightful obsession with this muddy concoction, here are our favorite coffee quotes to get you up and running for the day.'),
    (28,19,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2018/02/reading-book.jpg','collections/notable-quotes-quotations-themselves','19 Notable Quotes About Quotations Themselves','Quotations are often a great resource for better expressing ourselves. Their ability to encompass entire ideas in just a few words is what makes them so highly sought-after.\r\n\r\nWe use them in our speeches, articles, internet messages, and in both casual and academic settings.\r\n\r\nIn fact, quotes are so popular that they themselves have become a source of conversation, which is why we took it upon ourselves to collect these notable quotes about... quotations.'),
    (29,22,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2020/08/military-veteran-standing-in-front-of-us-flag.jpg','collections/triumphant-veterans-day-quotes','Triumphant Veterans Day Quotes','Six months ago we honored those who died in battle with 25 Glorious Memorial Day Quotes. However, despite the widespread confusion, Veterans Day is actually a completely separate holiday. While Memorial Day is a day for remembering those who died in the service of their country, Veterans Day is generally a time to thank living veterans for their service.\r\n\r\nTo show our appreciation and acknowledgement of the sacrifices and contributions made by all those who served honorably in the military, here are 24 triumphant Veterans Day quotes.\r\n\r\nThank you!'),
    (30,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/06/happy-labor-day-on-chalkboard.jpg','collections/celebratory-labor-day-quotes','Celebratory Labor Day Quotes','Labor Day marks many things: shopping and sales, the end of summer, the beginning of a new school year, football season, and a three-day weekend. But most importantly, it is a time to pay tribute to the working men and women whose contributions have brought prosperity.\r\n\r\nWhile we prepare for a long weekend of leisure, here are 50 celebratory Labor Day quotes for those of us who appreciate hard work (and a bit of procrastination).'),
    (31,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2013/04/funny-dog.jpg','collections/top-funny-quotes-all-time','Top 10 Funny Quotes of All-Time','Funny quotes are great for bringing a bit of humor into our lives. They help to lighten the mood, they\'re excellent for breaking the ice, and of course, they\'re fun to share with friends. After all, as Victor Borge once said, \"Laughter is the shortest distance between two people.\"\r\n\r\nSome of the most entertaining quotes, in our opinion, are those that are not only witty, but also wise — conveying some universal truth. Funny quotes about life, love, and friendship — those that we can relate to — are especially comical. Kurt Vonnegut once quipped, \"The best jokes are dangerous, and dangerous because they are in some way truthful.\"\r\n\r\nIn this list of 100 funny quotes worth laughing over, we\'ve tried to include a zinger for everyone, whether it\'s an insightful quotation, a silly saying, or an ironic wisecrack.');
INSERT INTO `topic` VALUES
    (1,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/02/dreams.jpg','topics/dreams','Dreams','Dreams are what keep us going. They’re a reflection of who we are, what we want to be and what we want from life. Our dreams, hopes and aspirations keep the fire burning inside us and motivate us to keep going even when everything seems futile. Our quotes prove just how powerful dreams can be, when backed with firm beliefs and convictions. '),
    (2,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/02/success.jpg','topics/success','Success','Success is one of the most misinterpreted concepts in modern times. The idea that success can only be measured in material terms is drilled into our mind from a very young age, and reinforced throughout our life. There are some, however, who take success as the ability and freedom to do whatever one wants, while being self-sustainable and living comfortably without hurting others. Our quotes on success offer insights on all perspectives.'),
    (3,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/03/pain.jpg','topics/pain','Pain',''),
    (4,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/03/motivation.jpg','topics/motivation','Motivation','Motivation is key to performance. Without the proper motivation, the simplest of tasks can seem burdensome. On the other hand, even seemingly unobtainable goals come within reach with the right words and right rewards. Motivation is especially important in competitive arenas such as sports, academics and business, and other settings where drive and attitude are especially important. Take a look at our quotes on motivation to see how it can impact performance.'),
    (5,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/03/fear.jpg','topics/fear','Fear','One of the most primal of emotions, fear rears its ugly head in many forms. For the reluctant flyer, it can be the anxiety before a business trip overseas. For the introvert, it can be the feeling of dread and doom before a public speech. From feelings of unease to crippling terror at the face of life-threatening situations, fear can debilitate and degrade quality of life. Our quotes may help you see the only thing to fear is fear itself.'),
    (6,50,'https://img.quotery.com/pictures/2014/02/love.jpg','topics/love','Love','Ah, love. Throughout the ages, no other emotion has inspired such a rich and diverse repertoire of literature, music, the arts…and love quotes. Philosophers to mystics to writers and artists, there are as many different interpretations as there are interpreters. Whether we’re able to articulate it as well as some, we all have our own take on what it means to love and to be loved. And love quotes from our leading thinkers may help us better understand love in our own life.');
