    (3212,'Never trust anything that can think for itself if you can\'t see where it keeps its brain.',50),
    (3213,'It\'s a strange thing, but when you are dreading something, and would give anything to slow down time, it has a disobliging habit of speeding up.',50),
    (3214,'It takes a great deal of courage to stand up to your enemies, but even more to stand up to your friends.',50),
    (3215,'Are you planning to follow a career in Magical Law, Miss Granger?” asked Scrimgeour. No, I’m not,” retorted Hermione. I’m hoping to do some good in the world!',50),
    (3216,'It was important, Dumbledore said, to fight, and fight again, and keep fighting, for only then could evil be kept at bay, though never quite eradicated. . . .',50),
    (3217,'So why in the name of Merlin’s saggy left —” Don’t talk to your mother like that.',50),
